items.title: H-1B visa: $100,000 fee a one-time payment, existing holders won't be charged, says White House
items.description: White House press secretary said that the new rule applies only to new applicants and not current visa holders

items.title: 60% of Indian H-1B workers earned $100,000 or less in FY24, says report
items.description: In comparison, 60 percent of the total non-Indian H-1B workers had salaries of more than $100,000 in FY24

items.title: Noida Airport set to begin operations post-Diwali; foreign airlines in talks for flight services
items.description: Noida Airport: The next major milestone is the issuance of the aerodrome licence by the Directorate General of Civil Aviation (DGCA)

items.title: Hospitals' body AHPI, Star Health to restore cashless services at member hospitals from October 10
items.description: The decision follows extensive discussions between the two sides, with AHPI agreeing to revoke its earlier advisory that had called for a suspension of cashless services from September 22.
